Just for your information.   If you book a party and leave a deposit - even though they tell you that they will refund your deposit - no problem. They lie.  You will get a gift certificate.   During the pandemic - I booked a small baby shower 4 mos. in advance and left a deposit.  I repeatedly asked the gentleman that took the reservation that in case the virus gets worse and I have to cancel - will I get my money back.   His answer was NO PROBLEM.  Well, of course, with the virus still raging - I had to cancel the party and in no way, shape or form did I get the deposit back.  He gave me a gift certificate for future use.    He said we NEVER GIVE MONEY BACK.    So  just be aware before you book anything.

What can I say about Europa.. I honestly want to give it a better rating than 3 stars, but I just don't feel I can. Quite plainly, the pizza is never fantastic. My favorite, the margherita pizza, is usually quite good but everything usually falls flat. And I do mean quite literally. I've had crispy pizza slices that could hold their own when they're in hand, but these are just wimpy. Every time I cut into the pizza I'm disappointed by how soggy it is. Their wine selection also leaves much to be desired along with the quality of the wine that's served. I guess the allure of the place is how nice it is inside and how appealing it looks from outdoors. Would I come here for a quick pizza? Maybe. Would I come here to impress? Probably not.

The food is always excellent and the service, although young and sometimes inexperienced is pleasant and friendly. I only have one gripe that mostly pertains to families with young children. The prices are very high for most everything. I understand they need to keep the lights on and the level of service high, so I accept that. Also the quantity of food is generous for the price. The exception is pasta dishes, which are way too small for the prices charged. Again, I'm fine if they need to charge those prices, but when my 10 year old walks away still hungry, that's a problem. I go out with the kids so I don't have to cook, so when he's still hungry after a meal, then there's no point in us going out. We're taking about basic pasta here; The cheapest, easiest item to prepare. I just need my kids to eat so I can relax, so please give larger pasta servings while keeping the prices where they are so I don't need to cook again when we get home! Or charge less so I can buy two servings. We would come here way more often if my kids didn't leave hungry when we left. Surprisingly, as I mentioned, the standard meals are generous, so that's why my complaint only pertains to easy-peazy pasta. The pizza is a specialty and a must have.

We didn't argue and just paid but honestly it's the principal (I would have likely left more). I took parts of my meal to go and it seemed like they just dumped it off the plate into the box and to me that was essentially the icing on the cake. Honestly I might give them another chance some time in the future and update this review but as it stands I wasn't pleased with the wait-staff, their lack of care and overall the experience. Pizza being the one saving factor hence 3-star not 1-star (I don't believe a business should be damaged over the poor performance of a lackluster employee or two and should have a chance to improve from customer criticism).
